{"id":18177441,"date":"2025-08-21T12:44:29","date_gmt":"2025-08-21T07:14:29","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/?p=18177441"},"modified":"2025-08-21T12:46:33","modified_gmt":"2025-08-21T07:16:33","slug":"difference-between-ca-and-acca","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/difference-between-ca-and-acca","title":{"rendered":"What is the difference between CA and ACCA?\u00a0"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Are you looking for a career in accounting or finance? The two most dominant qualifications to take this dream forward would be to choose between ACCA vs CA in India. With these rewarding careers lined up, it opens exciting doors for a promising future, helping individuals carve a successful life.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>But how do you choose? Which is better, CA or ACCA, or what are the global opportunities &#8211; CA vs ACCA hold? It might take a lot of time to ponder before landing on one option. This blog will help you align your career goals with your studies and also give a clear-cut picture of what works best for you.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What is a CA (Chartered Accountant)?&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/how-to-become-ca\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">CA or Chartered Accountant<\/a> is a designation awarded by the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI). It is a course where individuals can gain advanced knowledge in accounting with rigorous learning experience in audit, assurance, taxation, applied finance, and so on.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Prime aspects of the CA Course:<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Regulatory Body:<\/strong> ICAI, India\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Focus Areas:<\/strong> Indian Accounting Standards, Direct and Indirect Taxation, Corporate Laws, Auditing, and Financial Management\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Duration:<\/strong> Typically, 4\u20135 years (depending on attempts and completion of articleship)\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Course Levels:<\/strong> Foundation \u2192 Intermediate \u2192 Final\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Practical Training:<\/strong> Mandatory 3-year article ship under a practicing CA\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Being considered one of the hardest exams conducted in India, the passing percentage of the exam is also not very high. This brings in a high level of respect towards CA graduates.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>An interesting read: <\/strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/does-low-ca-pass-percentage-indicate-students-need-alternative-degree\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Why should CA aspirants consider earning an alternate degree?<\/strong><\/a><strong><\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What is ACCA (Association of Chartered Certified Accountants)<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/what-is-acca-a-complete-guide\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ACCA, or Association of Chartered Certified Accountants<\/a> is a qualification that encompasses several aspects of chartered accounting, such as business finance, auditing, taxation, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/scope-of-financial-management-as-a-career-choice\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">financial management<\/a> and so on. Originated from UK, unlike CA, ACCA is recognized by 180+ countries crafted for individuals interested in finance on a global stage.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Prime Aspects of the ACCA Course:<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Regulatory Body:<\/strong> Association of Chartered Certified Accountants, UK\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Focus Areas:<\/strong> IFRS (International Financial Reporting Standards), Audit, Financial Management, Performance Management, and Global Taxation Principles\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Duration:<\/strong> 2\u20133 years on average\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Course Levels:<\/strong> Applied Knowledge \u2192 Applied Skills \u2192 Strategic Professional\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Practical Training:<\/strong> 3-year Practical Experience Requirement (PER) can be completed in any approved organization worldwide\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>ACCA qualification provides flexibility for its students, where they can appear for exams four times a year and also finish the course at their own pace.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Give this a try: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/acca-papers-integrated-with-bcom\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">How Online BCom with ACCA Paper Integration Offers Financial and Career Benefits<\/a>\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">CA vs ACCA: Key Differences&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When it comes to the question of which is better, CA or ACCA, it depends purely on certain factors. Here\u2019s a quick side-by-side comparison:&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th><strong>Factor<\/strong>\u00a0<\/th><th><strong>CA (Chartered Accountant)<\/strong>\u00a0<\/th><th><strong>ACCA (Association of Chartered Certified Accountants)<\/strong>\u00a0<\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Governing Body<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>ICAI (India)&nbsp;<\/td><td>ACCA, UK&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Recognition<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Highly recognized in India&nbsp;<\/td><td>Recognized in 180+ countries&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Primary Focus<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Indian laws, taxation, and accounting standards&nbsp;<\/td><td>International laws, IFRS, and global finance&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Course Duration<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>4\u20135 years&nbsp;<\/td><td>2\u20133 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Flexibility<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Fixed schedule, strict deadlines&nbsp;<\/td><td>Flexible exam sittings (4 times\/year)&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Levels<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Foundation \u2192 Intermediate \u2192 Final&nbsp;<\/td><td>Applied Knowledge \u2192 Applied Skills \u2192 Strategic Professional&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Practical Training<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>3-year articleship in India&nbsp;<\/td><td>3-year PER (global options)&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Pass Rates<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Lower (often below 10% at Final level)&nbsp;<\/td><td>Higher (40\u201350% on average)&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Cost<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>\u20b92\u20133 lakhs (approx.)&nbsp;<\/td><td>\u20b93\u20134 lakhs (approx.)&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Ideal For<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Careers in Indian corporates, firms, and public sector&nbsp;<\/td><td>International career in MNCs, Big 4, and overseas firms&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now let\u2019s delve into the detailed differences between ACCA vs CA.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Read more: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/bcom-subjects-for-acca\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Which B.Com subjects will help in ACCA?<\/a>\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Governing Body and Recognition&nbsp;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Since CA is regulated by the ICAI, which is a statutory body in India, the chances for qualified candidates to work outside India are quite limited. But in India, this is recognized as one of the most prestigious governing bodies.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>An interesting read: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/indias-soaring-demand-for-cas\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">India\u2019s Soaring Demand for Chartered Accountants: Insights from CFO Balaji Iyengar<\/a>\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the other hand, a global qualification like ACCA&nbsp;is most probably recognized across Europe, the Middle East, Africa, Asia, and Australia. This is most probably one of the most preferred options for students, as they can opt to work abroad.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Syllabus and Subjects&nbsp;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>There is a huge difference between the CA and ACCA syllabus. Since every country is tailored to have different financial regulations, the syllabus of CA is aligned as keeping the Indian regulation in process. This includes even the corporate law, taxations and many more.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The ACCA is a qualification widely recognized in several countries. Hence, it leans more towards <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/what-is-corporate-accounting-definition-importance-and-process\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">international accounting standards<\/a>, providing a broader financial strategy that helps candidates become acquainted with global corporate environments.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Duration and Flexibility&nbsp;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>CA is a very arduous degree to complete, as it takes nearly 4-5 years or more. This aligns with the way exams are scheduled, as they are fixed, and the requirement of mandatory articleship. It may be structured, but it definitely is a very demanding path to travel.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>ACCA, on the other hand, can be completed within 2-3 years. This is due to the modular structure and the multiple sittings per year. This, in turn, offers greater flexibility for working professionals, helping them to take the exam at their own pace.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Practical Training\u00a0<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>While preparing for the course, candidates are required to have a mandatory three years of articleship under a practicing CA or a CA firm in India. This helps them gain exposure to the real CA world even before they enter it.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For ACCA, a three-year work experience, known as the Practical Experience Requirement (PER), is mandated by ACCA Global. This experience must be completed with an approved global organization. Additionally, experience in international markets is a significant advantage.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Pass Rates and Difficulty&nbsp;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This year, it was reported that around <a href=\"https:\/\/www.indiatoday.in\/education-today\/news\/story\/chartered-accountancy-final-2025-2-of-top-3-rankers-from-mumbai-2752034-2025-07-07\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">14,247<\/a> students passed the final CA exam. And a total of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.accaglobal.com\/gb\/en\/news\/2025\/July\/June25_exams.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">4,527<\/a> students completed the final ACCA exam.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The pass rates of CA when compared to the students attending it are only below 10%. Being one of the toughest exams and a reputable qualification, the difficulty and pass rates are justified.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>ACCA, on the other hand, comes to around 40-50%. This gives students the chance to achieve it more when compared to CA. Though easy when compared to its contemporaries, it is still a challenging course to pass.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Cost of the Course&nbsp;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The cost of preparing a CA course is significantly less compared to other degrees or contemporary courses. If the learner intends to pursue self-study, then the exam fees of approximately 86,500, as directed by the ICAI, are sufficient. However, if they plan to pursue coaching, the cost could be around \u20b91.5\u20132.5 lakh.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>ACCA falls on the pricey side when compared to CA. According to ACCA Global, the course costs approximately \u20b91.3\u20131.7 lakh. However, with the expenses of coaching classes and other costs, the total amount can reach a higher sum of \u20b92\u20133 lakh or more.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Career Opportunities and Salary&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When discussing the ACCA vs. CA salary comparison, it is often assumed that CA-qualified candidates earn more than ACCA-qualified candidates. However, when it comes to global opportunities of CA vs ACCA, both courses have a great deal to offer.&nbsp; ACCA qualified candidates can get to work with international taxation and regulation laws, while a CA certified indivdual concentrates more on the Indian accounting system.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">CA Careers&nbsp;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Audit firms\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Tax consultancy\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Indian corporates\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Government and public sector\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Independent practice\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">CA Salary&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>For a freshly qualified Chartered Accountant (CA) in India, the starting package can range from 6 to 8 LPA. As they gain more experience, mid-to-senior professionals can move on to salaries of 12-20 LPA.&nbsp; Furthermore, for partners and top executives, the annual package can range from \u20b9 40 lakhs to up to \u20b9 1 crore.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Give this a read: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/naina-goel-a-seasoned-chartered-accountant-and-budding-youtuber\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Meet Naina Goel: A seasoned CA and a budding, aspiring YouTuber<\/a>\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">ACCA Careers&nbsp;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Big 4 accounting firms\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Multinational corporations\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>International banks\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Global audit and consulting roles\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">ACCA Salary&nbsp;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Candidates who have qualified freshly after completing an ACCA course can expect a package of \u20b94\u20137 lakh per year, which depends solely on the organization. Once they reach a mid-senior level, \u20b97\u20138 lakh per year is a standard package. While CA generally offers higher salary growth within India, ACCA provides the advantage of global recognition and opportunities abroad.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Which One Should You Choose?&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>It can be a significant question mark when it comes to choosing between ACCA and CA in India. But let us help you here. The points below work to your benefit and will help lead you to take a route that suits you best.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Choos CA if:&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Looking to stay back in Inda\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Having a strong interest in the Indian taxation and corporate laws\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Ready to take up on a highly competitive exam.\u00a0\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>In search of a cost-effective professional qualification\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Choose ACCA if:&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>You want global mobility in your career.\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>You prefer international accounting standards (IFRS).\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>You want more flexibility in scheduling exams.\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>You\u2019re aiming for a career in MNCs or Big 4 firms abroad.\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Also read: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/multiple-degrees-one-solutions-manipal-university-jaipurs-online-degrees\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Ambitious CA aspirants: Why did they choose Manipal University Jaipur\u2019s online degrees?<\/a>\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Final Thoughts&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Both CA and ACCA are prestigious; it all comes down to where you see yourself working and what kind of finance professional you want to become.&nbsp; If India is your primary focus, CA is unbeatable. But if you\u2019re dreaming of international opportunities, ACCA gives you the passport to a global career. Either way, both require dedication, discipline, and a clear career vision, so choose wisely and start your journey today.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Through <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Online Manipal<\/a>, Manipal Academy of Higher Education has been providing ACCA courses along with the newly launched <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-bcom-professional-mahe\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">BCom program<\/a>. This will help students obtain an ACCA qualification, along with a fully structured UG degree, from the comfort of their own home. Additionally, it offers several undergraduate and postgraduate courses that can provide a great foundation for candidates seeking to complete their CA course.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, hop on to the link now and explore the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/all-courses\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">various courses<\/a> that Online Manipal has to offer.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Are you looking for a career in accounting or finance? The two most dominant qualifications to take this dream forward would be to choose between ACCA vs CA in India. With these rewarding careers lined up, it opens exciting doors for a promising future, helping individuals carve a successful life.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 But how do you choose? [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":126,"featured_media":18178406,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[596,3],"tags":[19],"class_list":["post-18177441","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-bachelors-degree","category-online-learning","tag-online-degree"],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v27.5 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/product\/yoast-seo-wordpress\/ -->\n<title>What is the difference between CA and ACCA?\u00a0 - Online Manipal<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Confused about which course to pursue between CA and ACCA? Read through this blog and find out all the details about these courses and what suits you the best.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/18177441\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_GB\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"What is the difference between CA and ACCA?\u00a0 - Online Manipal\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Confused about which course to pursue between CA and ACCA? Read through this blog and find out all the details about these courses and what suits you the best.\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https:\/\/www